  "texts": [
    "foot_3 Therefore, the objective function is usually specified so it gives the same score to all DAGs in an equivalence class-a property known as score equivalence.",
    "Most commonly used scores do have this property.",
    "However, it is worth noting that approximate and exact algorithms that use score equivalent objective functions often just return a single result DAG.",
    "In that case, we should regard the output DAG as being a representative of the equivalence class to which it belongs.",
    "Indeed, the particular DAG within an equivalence class that the algorithm returns is usually just an artefact of the dataset (Constantinou et al. 2021b)."
  ],
